Sir Roger Penrose -LRB- born 8 August 1931 -RRB- is an English mathematical physicist , mathematician and philosopher of science .
He is the Emeritus Rouse Ball Professor of Mathematics at the Mathematical Institute of the University of Oxford , as well as an Emeritus Fellow of Wadham College .
Penrose is known for his work in mathematical physics , in particular for his contributions to general relativity and cosmology .
He has received several prizes and awards , including the 1988 Wolf Prize for physics , which he shared with Stephen Hawking for their contribution to our understanding of the universe .